---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import jjLookingOut from "/images/coast-ii.jpg?url";
---

<BaseLayout pageTitle="About">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-2xl">
      <h1
        class="mt-10 text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-accent sm:text-4xl"
      >
        mah mind is always buzzin
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-6 text-xl leading-8">
        Here's why I'm starting this blog, why I've included the features in it,
        and what I'm hoping to achieve.
      </p>
      <figure class="mt-10 border-l border-indigo-600 pl-9">
        <blockquote class="font-normal text-secondary">
          <p>
            As Lucretia Yaghjian reminds us, writing is an act of faith: “Faith
            in yourself as a writer; faith in the importance of what you are
            writing; faith that there will be an audience for what you will
            write; faith that your writing will contribute ultimately to the
            flourishing of those who read it; and finally, faith in the source
            of your desire to write.”
          </p>
        </blockquote>
        <figcaption class="mt-6 flex gap-x-4">
          <div class="text-sm leading-6">
            <strong class="font-normal text-base-content"
              >Pierce Taylor Hibbs</strong
            > – in "We Who Work With Words: Towards a Theology of Writing"
          </div>
        </figcaption>
      </figure>
